      "writtenOn": "2025-11-11T05:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, even on Windows, it is better to use python path found from $PATH by default as I assume that most users installed their python via recommended way from their organization. And they still get the same absolute path like `/usr/bin/python` on POSIX?\n\nIf you want to use relative path, is it possible to use \nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/docs/reference.md#var_python_path:~:text\u003dhelp%20%2D%2Droot%2Dpattern%22)-,script_executable,-%5Boptional%5D%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20By%20default\nin your `.gn` file?",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "603355fa_b4739cce",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001787
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-11T06:36:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Even when setting relative path using `python_path` in `.gn`, the python path stored inside `BuildSettings` will always be an absolute path due to this:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/setup.cc#353\n\nRegarding using the python path in $PATH, there are a few issues with this:\n\n1) it will not work with remote execution because the user may have python in any  arbitrary $PATH that does not match what\u0027s available on the remote worker.  Note that because GN *always* makes `python_path` absolute on Windows (see link above), we are unable to simply use `\"python.exe\"` and let $PATH figure it out.\n\n2) organizations that work on many different projects will have multiple versions of python being used, so it becomes much easier to place the appropriate python inside each project.  For example, chromium can do this in `src/third_party/depot_tools`",
      "parentUuid": "296e159b_5d04d181",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6ce03ec0_114948fb",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001787
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-11T06:39:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also, this CL doesn\u0027t affect users who are currently using python in $PATH because it only changes the behavior of when python is within the root directory",
      "parentUuid": "603355fa_b4739cce",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4f0a0eca_3a51d583",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000030
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-13T06:57:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, then can we keep using relative python path from `FindWindowsPython` ?",
      "parentUuid": "6ce03ec0_114948fb",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "acd2b2a8_070ff805",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001787
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-13T14:13:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe `FindWindowsPython` **must** return an absolute path because the `BuildSettings::python_path` is used in places which require an absolute path on Windows, for example:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/function_exec_script.cc#188\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/invoke_python.cc#23\n\nThis is the reason why my CL creates a separate variable called `python_path_for_ninja`, which will hold the python path that will be used *only* inside the ninja-generated files.\n\nNote that in almost all cases, `python_path` and `python_path_for_ninja` will be identical.  So this CL is effectively a no-op except for the case where:\n\n1) We are using Windows, *and*\n2) `python_path` happens to be within the `root_path`\n\nIf the above two conditions are true, then `python_path_for_ninja` will contain the relative path from the `build_dir` to `python_path`, which effectively makes the ninja files portable to other drives/machines/etc.",
      "parentUuid": "4f0a0eca_3a51d583",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3a198437_37530188",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000030
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-18T10:18:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e https://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/function_exec_script.cc#188\n\u003e https://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/invoke_python.cc#23\n\nI think we can use relative path there as we passed build dir as current working directory of process invocation?",
      "parentUuid": "acd2b2a8_070ff805",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "25a0b995_48f994d0",
        "filename": "/COMMIT_MSG",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 9,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001787
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-18T14:05:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It turns out we still need the absolute path of python for things like exec_script, even though we use build dir as the \"startup_dir\".\n\nThe reason is because \"startup_dir\" is only used to set the current working directory **inside** the child process.  It is not used as the starting point from which to look for the executable, which happens *before* the child process is started.",
      "parentUuid": "3a198437_37530188",
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
