      "writtenOn": "2025-11-11T06:36:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This looks like a good change, but would you mind if I did it in a separate CL?  The `BuildSettings::SetPythonPath` method is actually a replacement of the `BuildSettings::set_python_path` from the header file, which already used `const base::FilePath\u0026`, and there are many places that currently call it, so some of those places may need to be updated with `std::move` as well.  If possible, I\u0027d prefer to do that as a separate change since it is not directly related to this CL",
      "parentUuid": "baef1936_dd105574",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9ec404ae_a089314e",
        "filename": "src/gn/build_settings.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000030
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-13T06:57:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Separating CL to use `std::move` in caller side sounds good. But using pass by value can still be done in this CL without any disadvantage?",
      "parentUuid": "5f570565_afd874c3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4a0e4411_9e2d2530",
        "filename": "src/gn/build_settings.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001787
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-13T14:13:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I change to use pass by value, then it will change the semantics in every place where `BuildSetttings::set_python_path` was used.  One disadvantage would be in places like this, where an additional copy would be introduced:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/setup.cc#849\n\nAlso, it doesn\u0027t seem to be the convention in this source file to use pass-by-value.  For example, `SetRootPath` is not passing by value:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/build_settings.cc#34\n\nSo if we change `SetPythonPath` to pass by value, then we should do it for all the other functions as well for consistency.  Therefore, I think it would be better to make this kind of change in a separate CL since it could affect a lot of places in the codebase if we want to do it consistently.",
      "parentUuid": "9ec404ae_a089314e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 57
      },
      "revId": "f27f9c5db59999f9b87196bac4f11f3cb0e82309",
      "serverId": "c360c8e5-7aa8-3905-a7a0-810934766dac"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "47d35ed4_2a64e550",
        "filename": "src/gn/build_settings.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000030
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-11-18T10:18:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e One disadvantage would be in places like this, where an additional copy would be introduced:\nhttps://gn.googlesource.com/gn/+/refs/heads/main/src/gn/setup.cc#849\n\nNo, even if you recieve by value, you can remove one copy by using `std::move` when setting `python_path_` inside this function.\n\n\n\u003e Also, it doesn\u0027t seem to be the convention in this source file to use pass-by-value.\n\nThat\u0027s true, but I feel it is not straightforward if you have implementation without pass by value then change implementation and caller to use pass by value.\n\n\nAnd pass by value in this CL rather intends to leave optimize opportunify for future usage of this function rather than existing one.",
      "parentUuid": "4a0e4411_9e2d2530",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 57
      },
